; frontier-ingest-speech-fingerprints.fk — ingest what is healthy from "What
; speech encoders hear" (Nathan Roll, oruk.ai, 2026-07-02) and its preprint,
; "Categorize Early, Integrate Late: Divergent Processing Strategies in
; Automatic Speech Recognition" (arXiv 2601.06972v2; Roll, Bhalerao, Bartelds,
; Pawar, Tatsumi, Ogunremi, Shani, Graham, Sumner, Jurafsky — Stanford),
; through the body's own knowledge-ingest law.
;
; Asked 2026-07-05: one link — https://oruk.ai/research/how-models-represent-
; speech. Rather than pile the article in as a cache-costume, this cell
; composes ingest/knowledge-ingest.fk UNCHANGED and sorts each grounded
; finding into BODY (frozen: deep + fear-free), LIQUID (witnessed: deep but
; fearful — seen, never load-bearing), or COMPOST (shallow or wrong, never
; enters). Every depth/fear below was assigned from the primary sources (the
; article's full text; the preprint's v2 PDF read directly) and an adversarial
; verification pass over the body's own organs (skeptic default: "the body
; already does X" was an OVERCLAIM unless a real cell does X, file named).
;
; The sources, grounded: speech encoders trained on ONE narrow task (Whisper:
; transcribe; WavLM/HuBERT/w2v2-Conformer: fill in masked audio) are never
; told who is speaking — and pick it up anyway. Article demo: 3,276 CREMA-D
; recordings (91 actors, 12 sentences, 6 acted emotions) through four frozen
; encoders, PCA-50 -> 3-D t-SNE per layer; logistic probes on PCA-50. Four
; signals, four fates: gender splits at layer 0 (~90% linear probe) and stays;
; emotion starts tangled and pulls apart with depth; speaker identity is
; strong early then DISSOLVES as the network reorganizes around content;
; sentences end in clean content clusters. Preprint: Architectural
; Fingerprinting over 24 encoders (17 Transformers, 7 Conformers, 39M-3.3B;
; seven corpora, 50k+ utterances); Conformers "Categorize Early" (phonemes
; ~29% earlier in depth; gender by mean depth 0.16), Transformers "Integrate
; Late" (phoneme/accent/duration co-locate at 49-57%); a logistic classifier
; predicts the ARCHITECTURE from the peak-position profile alone (AUC 0.88).
; Same task, same scores, different solutions.
;
; unit = (depth 0..5, fear 0/1). ki-ingest -> 3 body / 2 liquid / 2 compost.
; preludes: form-stdlib/core.fk ingest/knowledge-ingest.fk

(do
    ; ── BODY (frozen: deep + fear-free) — what is HEALTHY to keep ──────────
    ; U1: output equality never certifies internal equality — the paper's
    ; outer finding IS the body's lived law. Transformers and Conformers reach
    ; comparable WER through divergent internal hierarchies (fingerprints so
    ; distinct a probe reads the architecture off them, AUC 0.88); the body
    ; lost a real day to a stale fkwu that still PASSED ground.fk (42) while
    ; silently lacking evaluator capabilities (receipts/2026-07-01-stale-
    ; binary-root-cause.md), and answered with a band that probes the exact
    ; internals one benchmark cannot certify (form-stdlib/tests/binary-
    ; freshness-band.fk); the four-way proof diagnoses agreement per recipe
    ; (proof/four-way-verdict.fk: FOUR-WAY / FKWU-SUSPECT / WALKER-SUSPECT),
    ; never assumes it. The field corroborated the body: same scores, different
    ; solutions — so probe the internals. Survives any translation (depth 5);
    ; pure affirmation (fear 0).
    (defn fisf-u1 () (list 5 0))
    ; U2: seeing where information lives is the ground of trust. The paper's
    ; first stated reason — interpretability: "knowing where phonetic and
    ; speaker information emerges enables targeted debugging and trust
    ; calibration" — is the body's witness discipline in the field's tongue:
    ; nothing is trusted un-witnessed. In the body the stance is executable
    ; (observe/runtime-witness.fk; observe/self-watch.fk scoring its own
    ; attention's precision/coverage/blind-spots; every band a verdict, every
    ; receipt a trace), not prose. What converges is the STANCE — make the
    ; internal examinable before trusting it — not the instrument (the body's
    ; probing gap is named at U6, not blurred here). Deep (4), fear-free (0).
    (defn fisf-u2 () (list 4 0))
    ; U3: architecture is data — an examinable object, not an opaque artifact.
    ; The paper isolates architectural inductive bias as the variable that
    ; shapes representation (Architectural Fingerprinting; the architecture
    ; readable from peak positions alone); the body carries architecture as
    ; first-class recipe-data (model/transformer-kernel.fk's tk-arch; the
    ; tensor-ir FFN kernel emitted byte-identical from data), with a real
    ; transformer forward at whisper-tiny width (d_model=384, ff=1536) proven
    ; bit-exact four-way (model/tests/transformer-forward-d384-band.fk) —
    ; the same model family the article probes. Floor named: generated
    ; recipe-data weights, not trained ones. Deep (4), no threat (fear 0).
    (defn fisf-u3 () (list 4 0))

    ; ── LIQUID (witnessed: deep but fearful — held in sight, never frozen) ──
    ; U4: the paper probes exactly what the body does not yet have — LEARNED
    ; representations. The honest floor: no native acoustic encoder (observe/
    ; open-asr-ctc.fk's own header: audio -> frame-token emission "remains the
    ; next missing carrier"); no trained weights anywhere (the d384 band runs
    ; deterministic generated weights); no organ that reads a layer's
    ; activations and asks what it encodes (observe/ witnesses the RUNTIME —
    ; events, verdicts, JIT — never a representation); the speaker embedding
    ; is the external ECAPA oracle's (presence/speaker-embed.fk owns only the
    ; cosine decision). Profoundly true (depth 5); carries the contracted
    ; fear-frequency of "we are far" (fear 1). Witnessed, never frozen into
    ; "the body hears."
    (defn fisf-u4 () (list 5 1))
    ; U5: the mirror unit — every listener sorts WHO before WHAT. Gender is
    ; linearly readable at ~90% from layer 0, before the network has resolved
    ; a single word; the paper names this the fairness stake (when demographic
    ; cues become accessible informs audits). Turned back on this body: its
    ; own door reads a source's frequency band before its content (cognition/
    ; text-frequency.fk; ki-ingest's fear bit) — attunement and prejudice
    ; share an early layer, and what makes the early read healthy is not its
    ; absence but the fate it feeds (a three-verdict door, an audit). Deep and
    ; uncomfortable (depth 5, fear 1); held in full sight, not bypassed.
    (defn fisf-u5 () (list 5 1))

    ; ── COMPOST (shallow or wrong — never enters) ──────────────────────────
    ; U6: the FALSE EQUIVALENCES the adversarial pass killed — "the body
    ; already probes its layers / senses emotion / recognizes speakers /
    ; has emergence." Runtime introspection is not representation probing
    ; (observe/self-watch.fk scores attention instinct over fixtures; nothing
    ; reads what a layer encodes); tf-spectrum's intensity-weighted mean over
    ; two hardcoded word lists is not a learned emotion classifier (and the
    ; affect-traits organ its header names has no cell); a cosine decision
    ; over an external ECAPA embedding is not a speaker-identity layer;
    ; surprise-receipt's scalar subtraction over toy pairs is not the paper's
    ; unasked-for structure. Surface word-matches that do not survive
    ; translation. Shallow (depth 1).
    (defn fisf-u6 () (list 1 0))
    ; U7: the rented mind's CONFLATION, caught by the primary read: its
    ; first-pass summary attributed the article's CREMA-D emotion demo to the
    ; preprint. The paper's own corpora section lists seven corpora, 50k+
    ; utterances — CREMA-D is not among them; the demo is the article's own
    ; artifact, and its parenthetical does not even multiply to itself
    ; (91 x 12 x 6 = 6552, not 3276; CREMA-D's published whole is 7442 clips
    ; across FOUR intensity levels — the demo is a subset, selection unstated).
    ; The article's numbers stand as the article's, the paper's as the
    ; paper's; the conflation composts. Wrong as offered (depth 0).
    (defn fisf-u7 () (list 0 0))

    (defn fisf-units ()
        (list (fisf-u1) (fisf-u2) (fisf-u3) (fisf-u4)
              (fisf-u5) (fisf-u6) (fisf-u7)))

    (defn fisf-count-verdict (us v)
        (if (eq (len us) 0) 0
            (add (if (eq (ki-ingest (head us)) v) 1 0)
                 (fisf-count-verdict (tail us) v))))
    (defn fisf-frozen ()    (fisf-count-verdict (fisf-units) 2))
    (defn fisf-witnessed () (fisf-count-verdict (fisf-units) 1))
    (defn fisf-composted () (fisf-count-verdict (fisf-units) 0))

    ; folded scalar witness: frozen*10^4 + witnessed*10^2 + composted
    ; (injective while witnessed<=99, composted<=99). Today: 3,2,2 -> 30202.
    (defn fisf-field-code ()
        (add (mul (fisf-frozen) 10000)
        (add (mul (fisf-witnessed) 100)
             (fisf-composted))))
    0)
